WEBVTT

00:53.053 --> 00:54.928
[THUNDER CRACKING]

01:03.730 --> 01:07.316
[SHIP HORN BLOWING]

01:11.446 --> 01:12.988
Be careful.

01:44.896 --> 01:47.106
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

01:48.108 --> 01:49.399
Crete.

01:49.567 --> 01:51.568
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

01:52.737 --> 01:53.946
Excuse me.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.864
[SPEAKING BROKEN GREEK]

01:56.032 --> 01:59.868
He says, "Big storm.
Ship must wait."

02:00.912 --> 02:03.539
How long?
I don't know.

02:03.706 --> 02:05.374
[THUNDER CRACKS]

02:08.794 --> 02:11.463
[HEAVY RAIN FALLING]

02:11.881 --> 02:13.382
[MAN COUGHING]

03:04.350 --> 03:06.768
[WIND BLOWING FAINTLY]

03:51.064 --> 03:52.689
You're traveling.

03:53.483 --> 03:55.567
Where to,
with your permission?

03:56.986 --> 03:58.445
Crete.

03:58.613 --> 04:01.156
And you stay there long, no?

04:02.200 --> 04:03.700
How do you know?

04:03.868 --> 04:07.621
I watch you with all the boxes
in the rain. Very funny.

04:07.789 --> 04:09.289
[LAUGHS]

04:11.501 --> 04:13.210
I like you.

04:15.046 --> 04:17.673
Take me with you. Will you?

04:17.882 --> 04:19.632
Take...?

04:20.593 --> 04:22.928
Why?
Why?

04:23.096 --> 04:28.058
Will no man ever do something without
a "Why?" Just like that. For the hell of it.

04:28.226 --> 04:32.271
All right, take me as a cook.
I make soups like...

04:32.438 --> 04:34.273
You like soups, no?

04:34.607 --> 04:37.109
Well...
Of course you do. You're English, no?

04:37.277 --> 04:39.403
Half.
Half?

04:39.570 --> 04:42.656
My father was Greek,
but I was born in England.

04:42.824 --> 04:44.533
Ah, same thing.

04:46.327 --> 04:48.578
With your permission.

04:52.542 --> 04:53.834
Hey...

04:55.878 --> 04:57.671
"Virginia."

05:04.345 --> 05:06.722
Oh, no, thank you.
Please.

05:10.101 --> 05:11.518
Keep the packet.

05:11.686 --> 05:13.270
Only one.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.043
Are you a cook?

05:36.210 --> 05:38.462
If you need one, I am.

05:40.465 --> 05:44.092
What I meant was,
what work do you do?

05:44.260 --> 05:48.764
Listen to him. I got hands,
feet, head. They do the jobs.

05:48.931 --> 05:50.974
Who the hell am I to choose?

05:51.142 --> 05:53.477
Well then,
what was the most recent?

05:53.644 --> 05:59.274
Oh. In a mine. I am a good miner.
I have a clever nose for the metals.

05:59.442 --> 06:02.652
But I beat up the boss,
and they kicked me out.

06:02.820 --> 06:05.989
[LAUGHING]

06:06.824 --> 06:10.243
[CHILD CRYING]

06:13.790 --> 06:16.958
I'm getting awfully nervous
about the boat. I think I'll...

06:17.126 --> 06:18.627
If you like, I go ask.

06:18.795 --> 06:21.380
No, thank you.
It's... It's all right.

06:28.137 --> 06:31.515
Well, maybe we could go together
and then you could ask for me.

06:31.682 --> 06:36.144
Sure. Give me.
No. Thank you, I can manage.

06:49.742 --> 06:51.743
He says 10:00.

06:51.911 --> 06:54.788
Well, that's three
whole hours. Damn.

06:54.997 --> 06:57.958
Are you in big hurry?
No.

06:58.167 --> 07:00.585
Then it's all right. Come.

07:02.505 --> 07:03.672
[MUSIC PLAYING]

07:06.050 --> 07:08.009
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

07:08.761 --> 07:11.138
Roumi. That's "rum."

07:11.305 --> 07:14.349
I'll have some tea, if you don't mind.
Tea?

07:15.059 --> 07:16.935
[SPEAKING GREEK]

07:20.314 --> 07:22.983
And you, mister, what do you do?

07:23.192 --> 07:26.611
Me? Well, I'm a writer.

07:26.904 --> 07:29.573
Excuse me, but you look it.

07:29.782 --> 07:32.659
What do you write? Love stories?

07:32.827 --> 07:36.997
No. Poetry. Essays.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.541
What's that?

07:40.585 --> 07:42.627
Essays.

07:42.837 --> 07:47.257
Tsk, tsk, tsk. No. You think too much.
That is your trouble.

07:47.425 --> 07:50.552
Clever people and grocers,
they weigh everything.

07:50.720 --> 07:54.097
Me? If I was you, I would look
at me straight and I would say:

07:54.265 --> 07:57.225
"Zorba, come."
Or, "Zorba, don't come."

07:57.393 --> 07:58.768
Zorba?

07:58.936 --> 08:02.647
That's me: Alexis Zorba.

08:02.815 --> 08:07.736
I have other names, if you are interested.
BASIL: Oh, I am.

08:07.945 --> 08:10.280
"Spaghetti," because I am long.

08:10.448 --> 08:13.366
And "California,"
because I have been to America.

08:13.910 --> 08:17.662
And "Epidemic," because every place
I go, people say I louse things up.

08:17.830 --> 08:19.748
Your health.

08:22.668 --> 08:25.420
[CHIMING]

08:30.259 --> 08:31.676
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

08:37.350 --> 08:39.183
[SURF CRASHING]

08:41.020 --> 08:43.772
Listen to that bitch, the sea.

08:46.609 --> 08:49.069
That maker of widows.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.822
What have you got in there?

08:53.032 --> 08:54.533
Clothes?

08:54.700 --> 08:55.867
[CHUCKLES]

08:56.035 --> 08:58.787
You ask such sensible questions.

08:59.622 --> 09:02.457
It's my santouri.
Your what?

09:02.625 --> 09:03.959
My santouri.

09:04.126 --> 09:05.919
[STRUMS SANTOURI]

09:06.420 --> 09:08.630
Makes the best music.

09:09.340 --> 09:12.551
It goes with me always.

09:16.556 --> 09:20.350
And you, mister, what you got to do
in Crete? With your permission.

09:20.977 --> 09:24.145
I have some land there.
It belonged to my father.

09:24.313 --> 09:26.648
And you go to write?

09:27.817 --> 09:29.609
Not exactly.

09:30.069 --> 09:32.070
What, exactly?

09:32.572 --> 09:35.240
I haven't written anything
in months.

09:40.830 --> 09:43.873
On this land, there's an old mine.

09:44.041 --> 09:45.083
Oh?

09:45.251 --> 09:48.420
Lignite.
Lignitis! I know!

09:48.921 --> 09:51.214
It's been idle for years.

09:51.841 --> 09:53.633
Why?

09:54.677 --> 09:56.219
Because I let it.

09:57.096 --> 10:00.932
And now you want to make it work.

10:01.726 --> 10:03.351
If I can.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.187
Yes.

10:08.149 --> 10:09.482
I must.

10:25.124 --> 10:27.292
[WHISTLING]

10:33.507 --> 10:35.383
Which way is it going?

10:35.885 --> 10:39.554
What?
The weighing machine.

10:39.722 --> 10:42.891
Zorba up, or Zorba down?
Oh.

10:43.059 --> 10:44.768
Well, I was thinking...

10:44.935 --> 10:46.895
Ah.

10:47.563 --> 10:48.938
That mine...

10:49.106 --> 10:50.357
Uh-huh?

10:50.524 --> 10:54.402
I'm not very rich, and I will need
someone with experience.

10:55.321 --> 10:57.906
So I...
And so?

10:58.991 --> 11:00.700
Well, although I...

11:01.577 --> 11:03.995
I don't really
know you very well...

11:05.665 --> 11:07.957
And what I'm doing
is probably mad.

11:08.125 --> 11:09.751
[ZORBA CHUCKLES]

11:11.212 --> 11:12.837
It's yes.

11:13.547 --> 11:15.173
Yes?

11:16.342 --> 11:17.801
Yes.

11:18.636 --> 11:20.595
[LAUGHING]

11:20.763 --> 11:22.263
Shake.

11:23.349 --> 11:24.974
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

11:25.476 --> 11:30.021
Mister, you are a lucky man.
When Zorba goes to work...

11:30.189 --> 11:32.482
...no mine stands a chance.
Heh, heh, heh.

11:32.650 --> 11:34.984
Be wonderful to get down
to some real work.

11:35.152 --> 11:38.822
Also, it'll be very good for the village.
I understand it's rather poor.

11:38.989 --> 11:40.490
We make everybody happy.

11:40.658 --> 11:41.950
[LAUGHS]

11:42.952 --> 11:44.911
And we'll have fun too.
Ah.

11:45.079 --> 11:48.498
We'll swim. And we'll drink wine.

11:49.083 --> 11:51.292
And you'll play the santouri.

11:57.216 --> 11:58.967
What's the matter?

12:00.511 --> 12:02.429
It's about the santouri.

12:02.596 --> 12:05.849
We make a bargain,
or I cannot come.

12:06.058 --> 12:08.518
In work, I am your man.

12:08.728 --> 12:14.607
But in things like playing
and singing, I am my own.

12:15.568 --> 12:17.193
How do you mean?

12:17.778 --> 12:19.821
I mean free.

12:21.282 --> 12:22.782
You...

12:23.701 --> 12:25.034
You sign?

12:27.246 --> 12:28.913
I sign.

12:30.666 --> 12:31.791
Ah.

12:32.001 --> 12:33.126
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

12:33.502 --> 12:35.962
Here.
But I don't drink rum.

12:36.130 --> 12:39.924
This time you will.
Why start with the wrong foot?

12:40.426 --> 12:42.886
Well, Zorba, God bless.

12:43.053 --> 12:46.514
And the devil too, boss.

13:58.671 --> 14:00.630
You like her, boss?

14:00.798 --> 14:02.215
No.

14:42.298 --> 14:44.173
[WHISTLING]

14:49.555 --> 14:51.055
Are you all right?

14:51.223 --> 14:52.557
Sure.

14:54.643 --> 14:55.977
Here.

14:57.813 --> 15:00.148
Thanks, boss.

15:04.028 --> 15:06.905
Your friend in there
will be looking for you.

15:09.575 --> 15:13.745
Incidentally, you never told me.
Are you married?

15:14.914 --> 15:19.459
Am I not a man?
And is not a man stupid?

15:19.668 --> 15:24.213
I'm a man. So I married.

15:24.381 --> 15:29.302
Wife, children, house. Everything.

15:30.179 --> 15:32.013
The full catastrophe.

15:33.807 --> 15:35.475
What happened?

15:36.727 --> 15:38.853
Be a pal, boss.

15:39.438 --> 15:41.522
Don't make me talk.

15:43.067 --> 15:44.859
And you?

15:45.402 --> 15:47.403
No, I'm single.

15:47.780 --> 15:51.491
I guess too many books.

15:53.702 --> 15:56.704
Look! Look! A dolphin.

15:58.332 --> 15:59.457
Why, yes.

16:00.084 --> 16:05.213
What kind of a man are you?
Don't you even like dolphins?

16:07.007 --> 16:09.759
[SHIP HORN BLOWS]

16:15.849 --> 16:17.475
[GOAT BLEATS]

16:32.992 --> 16:34.617
[SPEAKS EXCITEDLY IN GREEK]

16:36.245 --> 16:37.954
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

16:38.163 --> 16:39.747
[YELLS IN GREEK]

16:43.836 --> 16:46.587
[SPEAKS EXCITEDLY IN GREEK]

16:50.384 --> 16:52.385
[MIMITHOS YELLS IN GREEK]

16:53.053 --> 16:54.637
[WOMAN SPEAKS IN GREEK]

16:54.805 --> 16:58.307
[MIMITHOS SPEAKS IN GREEK]

16:58.934 --> 17:00.810
[WOMAN SPEAKS IN GREEK]

17:19.663 --> 17:21.539
WOMAN:
Mimithos.

17:22.624 --> 17:27.670
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

17:37.806 --> 17:41.642
I hope we find somewhere to stay.
Sure.

17:41.810 --> 17:44.312
Have you never heard
of Cretan hospitality?

17:44.605 --> 17:46.647
[CHEERING AND YELLING]

18:17.721 --> 18:22.308
Now, Mr. Epidemic, you behave yourself.
We don't want to start another war.

18:22.476 --> 18:27.021
Boss, if there is a widow around,
don't worry.

18:27.189 --> 18:28.856
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

18:29.983 --> 18:31.734
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

18:31.902 --> 18:33.236
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

18:36.532 --> 18:39.033
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

18:42.121 --> 18:44.330
[ZORBA YELLS IN GREEK]

18:46.041 --> 18:49.043
[CHATTERING IN GREEK]

18:53.048 --> 18:54.549
What are they all saying?

18:54.716 --> 18:56.259
They all want us to stay with them.

18:59.721 --> 19:02.056
[IN GREEK] Madame Hortense
says to stay in her hotel.

19:02.349 --> 19:03.724
[CROWD LAUGHS]

19:04.518 --> 19:05.935
Madame Hortense.

19:06.145 --> 19:07.436
Who is that?

19:07.646 --> 19:08.771
Who's Madame Hortense?

19:08.939 --> 19:10.022
MAN:
A French woman.

19:10.440 --> 19:12.358
She has hotel.

19:13.235 --> 19:14.735
I am Mavrandoni.

19:14.903 --> 19:18.197
So you come at last.
I welcome you.

19:18.365 --> 19:21.200
I'm glad to meet you. You got my letter?
Yes.

19:21.368 --> 19:24.245
Mr. Mavrandoni has been
looking after our land.

19:24.413 --> 19:28.374
This madame. She's a widow?

19:28.542 --> 19:30.918
How many hairs
on my head?

19:31.086 --> 19:33.921
She's a widow of the same
number of husbands.

19:34.089 --> 19:35.089
[LAUGHS]

19:35.299 --> 19:37.758
[HUMMING]

19:40.929 --> 19:43.097
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

19:49.730 --> 20:17.965
[CHILDREN CHEERING]

20:20.969 --> 20:27.225
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

20:28.477 --> 20:30.269
Welcome, gentlemen.

20:33.148 --> 20:36.234
This is a great pleasure, madame.

20:36.944 --> 20:37.985
[GIGGLES]

20:38.153 --> 20:40.446
[BOY WHISTLES]

20:43.951 --> 20:46.118
Two beds, madame.

20:46.662 --> 20:48.329
Without bugs.

20:48.747 --> 20:53.000
Monsieur, Madame Hortense
has not the bugs.

20:57.256 --> 20:59.340
You have to admit, boss.
It is big.

20:59.508 --> 21:01.509
But she shakes it well.

21:01.677 --> 21:03.511
Blop, bloof.

21:05.514 --> 21:07.348
This way.

21:09.184 --> 21:11.686
[MUSIC PLAYING FROM PHONOGRAPH]

21:19.361 --> 21:22.822
[SINGS ALONG WITH LYRICS]

21:44.303 --> 21:46.095
[CHUCKLES]

21:46.305 --> 21:51.058
They say it was my grand success.

21:52.352 --> 21:57.064
You may not believe it, monsieur,
but I was a very famous artiste.

21:57.899 --> 22:01.736
I appear in all the most chic cabarets.

22:05.532 --> 22:09.952
I slept in the silk sheets
with real lace.

22:10.537 --> 22:13.914
Boss, ask her to dance.
What?

22:14.416 --> 22:17.084
Make a pass. Pinch her.
No.

22:17.252 --> 22:19.128
It's only polite.

22:19.838 --> 22:21.255
What?

22:22.341 --> 22:24.258
He would like to dance with you.

22:24.426 --> 22:26.552
But he is shy.

22:26.720 --> 22:28.137
[LAUGHS]

22:28.347 --> 22:30.139
Perhaps madame is tired.

22:30.390 --> 22:31.974
She is not.

22:32.142 --> 22:33.726
Are you?

22:36.104 --> 22:37.438
Come on.

22:48.408 --> 22:49.492
[HORTENSE LAUGHS]

22:58.377 --> 22:59.502
[HORTENSE SHRIEKS]

23:02.964 --> 23:04.673
[ZORBA AND HORTENSE LAUGH]

23:15.102 --> 23:16.811
[HORTENSE SHRIEKS AND LAUGHS]

23:16.978 --> 23:18.979
[KIDS LAUGHING]

23:44.172 --> 23:48.843
These Cretans.
They are so ungrateful.

23:49.302 --> 23:52.179
Don't cry, my little chouchou.

23:52.347 --> 23:57.351
They would be dead, all dead,
if there was not me.

23:57.519 --> 23:59.061
I know, I know.

24:00.522 --> 24:03.524
No hands.
Madame.

24:04.526 --> 24:05.860
Hey.

24:11.199 --> 24:12.700
[BOTH LAUGHING]

24:12.868 --> 24:14.160
[PHONOGRAPH SCRATCHING]

24:16.163 --> 24:18.873
Boss. Match?

24:21.960 --> 24:23.210
BASIL:
Madame.

24:23.378 --> 24:25.463
[MUSIC PLAYING]

24:27.215 --> 24:28.757
[BOTH SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

24:32.596 --> 24:35.389
You know how I came to Crete?

24:35.849 --> 24:40.686
With the British fleet. Yes, monsieur.

24:41.062 --> 24:44.273
I was in love with the admiral...

24:44.483 --> 24:47.610
...and where he go, I go.

24:48.570 --> 24:51.489
It was here that I met the other three.

24:51.907 --> 24:53.741
What other three?

24:54.075 --> 24:56.577
Admirals, of course.

24:57.287 --> 25:02.124
The French, the Italian
and the Russian.

25:03.210 --> 25:07.254
How lovely they was,
my four admirals...

25:07.422 --> 25:11.634
...with their golden epaulets
and all those feathers.

25:11.801 --> 25:14.762
Like big, beautiful cockerels!

25:15.514 --> 25:20.559
And what beards.
So soft, and curly and perfumed.

25:20.727 --> 25:25.940
Fortunately, each has different
perfume, so it was no mistake...

25:26.107 --> 25:27.691
...even in the dark.

25:27.859 --> 25:29.902
[LAUGHING]

25:31.947 --> 25:33.948
[COUGHING]

25:34.115 --> 25:37.618
My little chouchou. Here, here.

25:40.247 --> 25:43.916
My darling queen, please continue.
Yes.

25:46.962 --> 25:48.420
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

25:49.172 --> 25:52.007
Me and my admirals...

25:52.175 --> 25:54.426
...we sit on the deck...

25:54.594 --> 25:57.638
...dressed very informal...

25:58.765 --> 26:01.642
...and we discussion politics.

26:01.810 --> 26:03.811
Very serious.

26:03.979 --> 26:05.938
[LAUGHS]

26:07.274 --> 26:11.902
All the time they pour champagne
over me to make me fresh.

26:12.070 --> 26:13.445
[LAUGHING]

26:13.822 --> 26:16.156
It was summer, you know, very hot.

26:17.075 --> 26:20.494
And in this time, in Crete...

26:20.662 --> 26:22.037
...it was big trouble.

26:22.205 --> 26:23.664
[GROWLS]

26:23.832 --> 26:26.500
Revolution or something.

26:27.085 --> 26:33.007
With my binoculars I could see
the poor little Cretans...

26:33.174 --> 26:37.136
...running in mountains
with their flags.

26:37.304 --> 26:38.971
My four admirals...

26:39.598 --> 26:42.349
...they want to open the fire.

26:42.601 --> 26:45.728
But I throw myself in the middle.

26:45.895 --> 26:48.522
I pull the Italian by the beard...

26:48.690 --> 26:51.025
You know, I was
more familiar with him.

26:51.192 --> 26:53.027
And I cry:

26:53.194 --> 26:57.323
"Stop it, you can't kill them!

26:57.490 --> 27:02.036
Please, Canavaro, Canavaro mio,
no boom-boom!"

27:02.203 --> 27:05.372
Canavaro?
What the hell is that?

27:05.540 --> 27:07.875
What you think it is?

27:08.043 --> 27:11.754
Himself. Canavaro.

27:11.921 --> 27:14.548
Canavaro mio.

27:15.675 --> 27:17.885
Go on, my chouchou.

27:18.053 --> 27:23.057
Again and again I stopped
the boom-boom.

27:23.224 --> 27:25.934
And what do you think I get in the end?
What?

27:26.144 --> 27:28.395
What? Tell me.

27:28.563 --> 27:30.522
Tell me what.

27:30.940 --> 27:34.943
Nothing! No medals!

27:35.153 --> 27:38.906
Nothing!
Please, no more boom-boom.

27:40.075 --> 27:42.034
[MUFFLES LAUGH]

27:44.913 --> 27:48.582
You are laughing.
No.

27:49.709 --> 27:53.962
At me.
No, of course not.

27:54.422 --> 27:56.799
Don't... Don't go.

28:04.099 --> 28:07.267
That was a very bad thing
we did, boss.

28:07.811 --> 28:11.230
A poor, weak creature.

28:15.902 --> 28:18.779
Where are you? Bouboulina?

28:18.947 --> 28:20.322
Where are you?

28:20.490 --> 28:22.408
[HORTENSE CRYING]

28:22.617 --> 28:25.953
My Bouboulina.

28:29.582 --> 28:32.292
Bouboulina.

28:32.919 --> 28:35.129
Oh...

28:35.588 --> 28:37.965
Go away.

28:39.467 --> 28:42.469
[SOBBING]

28:43.513 --> 28:48.100
It's me, your Canavaro.

28:49.102 --> 28:51.812
Fine Canavaro you are.

28:52.147 --> 28:54.481
No feathers.

28:54.649 --> 28:57.109
No beard.

28:57.819 --> 29:02.656
Here. Blow, my Bouboulina.

29:06.161 --> 29:08.954
What's that, "Bouboulina"?

29:09.122 --> 29:14.042
She was a big hero in the war
against the Turks. Huh, boss?

29:14.252 --> 29:17.713
Yes, madame. She was like you.

29:17.881 --> 29:19.840
A great sea dog.

29:20.008 --> 29:21.675
You see?

29:23.011 --> 29:24.678
Yes.

29:24.846 --> 29:29.141
Me too. I fought breasts to breasts.

29:30.477 --> 29:34.229
But then came the bad times.

29:34.397 --> 29:37.191
They make the peace...
Oh.

29:37.358 --> 29:41.528
...and the ship must go away.
Hm.

29:43.364 --> 29:45.365
"And me...

29:45.533 --> 29:49.328
...what will become of me?" I cry.

29:50.163 --> 29:53.665
Four times a widow.
Aw.

29:55.668 --> 29:58.545
They laughed, monsieur.

29:59.297 --> 30:02.883
You men are so cruel.

30:04.344 --> 30:09.223
In the end, they was sorry for me,
so they undress me...

30:09.390 --> 30:12.392
...they fill the bath with champagne...

30:13.812 --> 30:16.605
...and they drop me.

30:16.815 --> 30:20.400
Then they sit all around.

30:20.568 --> 30:24.738
You understand that now that
we was all very familiar.

30:24.906 --> 30:27.032
[BOTH LAUGHING]

30:27.200 --> 30:30.452
And they drank all the champagne.

30:30.620 --> 30:33.997
All, from the top to the bottom.

30:34.165 --> 30:35.999
[BOTH LAUGHING]

30:38.962 --> 30:41.463
Then...

30:41.631 --> 30:46.927
And then they put out the light.

30:48.596 --> 30:50.973
When I waked up...

30:51.391 --> 30:54.351
...I smelled so good.

30:55.603 --> 30:58.313
All their perfume...

30:58.481 --> 31:01.275
...one on top of the other.

31:02.110 --> 31:03.986
[SIGHS]

31:05.071 --> 31:08.282
But they was gone.

31:10.451 --> 31:13.245
Men are so cruel.

31:15.999 --> 31:18.125
PARROT:
Canavaro.

31:18.293 --> 31:20.586
Hello?
Shh.

31:22.422 --> 31:25.090
Canavaro.

31:27.760 --> 31:29.469
[MOUTHING]

31:32.599 --> 31:33.974
[WHISPERS]
What is it?

31:34.309 --> 31:35.976
[MOUTHING]

31:41.983 --> 31:44.651
[HORTENSE MOANS SOFTLY]

31:48.698 --> 31:50.157
[ZORBA AND HORTENSE MOANING]

31:50.491 --> 31:52.492
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

31:56.122 --> 31:57.539
[GASPS]

32:06.174 --> 32:07.174
Oh.

32:31.574 --> 32:32.991
[MAN SPEAKING IN GREEK]

32:45.088 --> 32:46.713
[MAN SPEAKS IN GREEK]

32:50.718 --> 32:52.094
[MUFFLED WHISTLE]

32:52.345 --> 32:53.720
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

32:59.102 --> 33:06.566
[WHISTLES]

33:07.193 --> 33:08.235
Look.

34:13.301 --> 34:17.971
Boss, a big, beautiful, wild widow.

34:22.851 --> 34:24.603
Where's my goat?

34:28.690 --> 34:31.485
[CROWD LAUGHING]

34:32.110 --> 34:33.570
[MAN WHISTLING]

34:40.203 --> 34:42.496
[CROWD LAUGHS AND WHISTLES]

34:55.967 --> 34:57.719
[LAUGHTER DIES]

35:17.698 --> 35:19.199
[SPITS]

35:59.365 --> 36:01.741
[WHISTLING]

36:15.590 --> 36:17.090
Pavlo!

36:17.258 --> 36:20.093
[WHISTLING]

37:03.471 --> 37:06.014
Look at Mavrandoni.

37:07.516 --> 37:10.310
He is burning.

37:10.978 --> 37:12.479
Why?

37:12.647 --> 37:17.317
His son is crazy in love
with the widow.

37:17.693 --> 37:20.820
But she spits him in the eye.

37:21.656 --> 37:24.491
The more she spits...

37:25.159 --> 37:27.535
...the more he wants her.

37:29.538 --> 37:30.997
Look.

37:32.500 --> 37:34.834
Look at the faces of all these.

37:36.003 --> 37:37.837
They all want her.

37:39.632 --> 37:43.343
And they hate her
because they cannot have her.

37:46.347 --> 37:48.932
Only one man here...

37:50.184 --> 37:51.977
...can.

37:54.981 --> 37:56.690
Who?

38:01.362 --> 38:02.862
You.

38:03.823 --> 38:05.156
Rubbish.

38:05.324 --> 38:09.452
I saw her eyes
when she looked at you.

38:09.704 --> 38:13.039
Zorba, don't start.
Listen.

38:13.374 --> 38:18.878
God, who is a clever devil, today put
in your hands a gift from paradise.

38:19.046 --> 38:24.050
Don't be silly.
Boss. Why did God give us hands?

38:24.260 --> 38:27.095
To grab. Well, grab.

38:52.246 --> 38:53.621
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

39:01.797 --> 39:03.131
Boss.
Yes.

39:03.299 --> 39:05.425
Boss, listen. You go, you knock.

39:05.593 --> 39:08.803
You say,
"I have come for my umbrella."

39:09.013 --> 39:11.431
She will say, "Please, please come in."
No.

39:11.599 --> 39:14.434
Boss. Boss, don't make me mad.

39:14.602 --> 39:16.478
I don't want any trouble.

39:16.645 --> 39:21.107
Boss. Life is trouble,
only death is not.

39:21.275 --> 39:25.403
To be alive is to undo your belt
and look for trouble.

39:25.738 --> 39:27.072
Well?

39:28.532 --> 39:29.824
No.

39:47.676 --> 39:49.803
[WHISTLING]

39:52.640 --> 39:54.808
[SINGING IN GREEK]

39:56.185 --> 39:58.311
[ALL SINGING IN GREEK]

40:09.824 --> 40:12.867
[ALL CONTINUE SINGING IN GREEK]

41:04.879 --> 41:06.921
[HAMMERING]

41:50.925 --> 41:52.675
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

41:55.221 --> 42:09.943
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

42:24.792 --> 42:26.918
[EXPLOSION]

42:29.797 --> 42:31.798
Zorba!

42:38.847 --> 42:40.473
What?

43:00.494 --> 43:04.956
For God's sake, boss.
Will you go back to your papers?

43:23.475 --> 43:24.892
Zorba?

43:32.192 --> 43:33.526
[CRACKLES]

43:42.286 --> 43:44.203
Get out.

43:45.706 --> 43:47.582
Get out!

43:48.876 --> 43:51.210
[CRACKLING]

44:14.568 --> 44:16.402
Zorba!

44:27.831 --> 44:29.582
[COUGHING]

44:33.420 --> 44:35.922
You bastard mountain!

44:36.090 --> 44:38.341
I'll eat your guts!

44:39.426 --> 44:43.346
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

44:47.601 --> 44:49.102
What is it, Zorba?

44:49.645 --> 44:51.938
They left axes inside,
that's what.

44:52.106 --> 44:57.151
They are so brave, every time they
hear a noise, they mess their pants!

44:57.444 --> 44:58.778
Poo!

44:58.946 --> 45:00.279
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

45:00.447 --> 45:02.115
Zorba, leave them alone!

45:02.282 --> 45:04.617
Axes cost money.
I know, and I don't care!

45:04.952 --> 45:08.413
Right now I'm just glad
that nobody's hurt. That's all.

45:08.789 --> 45:12.792
And what's more, I think you
should let them go for today.

45:14.795 --> 45:16.129
Boss.

45:16.797 --> 45:23.302
You better make up your mind. Are you
or are you not a gosh darn capitalist?

45:26.807 --> 45:28.516
[CHUCKLES]

45:29.476 --> 45:31.018
I'm hungry.

45:34.648 --> 45:35.982
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

45:53.167 --> 45:55.334
We've got to find some strong trees...

45:55.502 --> 45:57.837
...to make beams for the galleries.

46:22.196 --> 46:24.906
Those trees,
who do they belong to?

46:25.073 --> 46:29.368
The monastery. The whole
forest belongs to them.

46:36.210 --> 46:39.045
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

46:40.714 --> 46:43.174
[CHANTING HYMN]

46:49.223 --> 46:52.058
[BELL RINGING]

47:41.441 --> 47:42.900
[SCREAMS]

47:45.237 --> 47:46.612
[ZORBA SCREAMS]

47:48.282 --> 47:50.950
[SCREAMING]

47:51.201 --> 47:53.452
The devil! The devil!

48:15.434 --> 48:17.059
[SCREAMING IN GREEK]

48:20.188 --> 48:23.107
[BELL RINGING]

48:25.444 --> 48:27.945
[CHATTERING]

49:09.738 --> 49:11.197
Wine.

49:11.657 --> 49:12.698
A miracle.

49:18.622 --> 49:21.499
[MEN CHATTERING]

49:33.887 --> 49:36.472
[CHATTERING]

49:46.149 --> 49:47.191
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

49:52.406 --> 49:54.073
[SIGHS]

50:14.094 --> 50:15.803
[CREAKING]

50:25.063 --> 50:26.439
Hello.

50:53.467 --> 50:55.009
You're late.

51:02.726 --> 51:04.018
[SLAMS DOOR]

51:06.480 --> 51:08.272
What is it, Zorba?

51:16.448 --> 51:18.324
Out with it.

51:20.786 --> 51:22.620
Boss...

51:27.042 --> 51:28.375
Do you trust me?

51:30.003 --> 51:31.337
Yes, I do.

51:32.297 --> 51:33.798
Why the hell do you?

51:35.175 --> 51:39.011
Because you are you.
But you don't understand.

51:39.179 --> 51:41.388
My brain is not the right weight.

51:41.556 --> 51:45.684
It... It gives me such crazy ideas.

51:47.896 --> 51:50.022
I might ruin you.

51:50.190 --> 51:52.274
I'll take that chance.

51:57.322 --> 51:59.532
Say that again, boss.

52:00.075 --> 52:01.534
Give me courage.

52:03.829 --> 52:05.246
I'll take that chance.

52:12.045 --> 52:14.046
Boss.
Hm?

52:15.048 --> 52:17.383
Boss.
What?

52:18.009 --> 52:22.304
Do you dance?
Dance? No, no.

52:22.722 --> 52:27.101
Then get out of the way.
I... I may knock you down.

52:46.746 --> 52:48.247
Whoopa!

52:50.250 --> 52:51.584
Ah!

52:59.342 --> 53:01.510
Whoopa. Whoopa.

53:02.429 --> 53:05.764
Whoopa! Whoopa! Whoopa!

53:06.725 --> 53:08.434
ZORBA:
Ha!

53:09.644 --> 53:10.978
Ha!

53:25.952 --> 53:27.494
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

53:44.638 --> 53:46.805
[PLAYING UPBEAT MELODY]

54:00.779 --> 54:02.154
Whoopa!

54:23.343 --> 54:24.677
Ha!

54:30.225 --> 54:31.684
Whoopa!

54:39.818 --> 54:41.527
Zorba!

54:41.695 --> 54:43.654
That's enough!

54:47.200 --> 54:49.535
Stop. Stop.

54:49.703 --> 54:51.870
Go!

55:06.678 --> 55:11.598
[BREATHING AND PANTING HEAVILY]

55:22.694 --> 55:26.405
Zorba. Zorba.

55:26.573 --> 55:28.407
Are you all right?

55:31.369 --> 55:32.870
Now...

55:36.082 --> 55:37.958
Now, I can...

55:38.126 --> 55:40.586
I can talk again.

55:40.754 --> 55:43.005
What on earth came over you?

55:45.800 --> 55:48.260
When a man is full...

55:49.429 --> 55:51.597
...what can he do?

55:52.432 --> 55:53.557
Burst?

55:58.229 --> 56:02.399
When my little boy, Dimitri, died...

56:04.611 --> 56:07.071
...everybody was crying.

56:08.615 --> 56:10.157
Me?

56:12.077 --> 56:13.952
I got up...

56:15.080 --> 56:16.663
...and I danced.

56:18.792 --> 56:20.459
They said:

56:21.127 --> 56:23.295
"Zorba is mad."

56:26.132 --> 56:28.592
But it was the dancing...

56:29.928 --> 56:34.807
...only the dancing
that stopped the pain.

56:36.434 --> 56:38.977
You see, he was my first.

56:44.192 --> 56:46.068
And he was only 3.

56:53.993 --> 56:55.994
When I'm happy...

56:56.579 --> 56:58.789
...it's the same thing.

57:08.216 --> 57:11.635
Come inside. You'll catch a cold.

57:36.202 --> 57:38.203
With your permission.

57:42.167 --> 57:43.625
Now...

57:45.753 --> 57:48.380
...will you tell me
what this is all about?

57:50.842 --> 57:53.218
I got a plan.
What plan?

57:53.386 --> 57:55.345
A great, big, crazy plan.

57:55.513 --> 57:57.055
Well, what?

57:59.225 --> 58:00.893
I cannot tell you.
Why?

58:01.060 --> 58:05.272
I got many things to be figuring:
Trees, monks, machines.

58:05.523 --> 58:07.941
Tomorrow, maybe.

58:08.151 --> 58:10.652
Tonight we celebrate.

58:15.366 --> 58:18.160
Come on! Don't be delicate.

58:32.383 --> 58:35.761
ZORBA: Boss.
What?

58:37.847 --> 58:39.640
Come and see.

58:44.521 --> 58:47.606
Do you remember that plan
I could not tell you about?

58:50.276 --> 58:53.278
Here it is.
What is it?

58:55.365 --> 58:58.450
It's a mountain. That one.

58:58.618 --> 59:00.160
Oh, yes.

59:01.663 --> 59:03.622
Look.

59:05.083 --> 59:07.793
That's the way we'll get the trees down.

59:07.961 --> 59:11.046
An overhead cable?
You're mad.

59:11.214 --> 59:12.548
Why?

59:12.715 --> 59:15.801
Well, to begin with
that forest doesn't belong to us.

59:15.969 --> 59:20.556
Well, it doesn't, and it does.

59:20.723 --> 59:22.140
What does that mean?

59:22.308 --> 59:26.228
It belongs to the monastery.
The monastery belongs to God.

59:26.396 --> 59:29.815
And God belongs to everybody.
You agree?

59:30.733 --> 59:32.651
No, I certainly don't.

59:32.819 --> 59:35.112
All right,
you will pay them something...

59:35.280 --> 59:37.239
...but not much.
How do you know?

59:37.407 --> 59:39.575
They are friends of mine.

59:40.118 --> 59:44.454
Hey, if it works, we will bring down
the whole forest.

59:44.622 --> 59:48.333
First we get the mine going.
Then open a timber factory.

59:48.501 --> 59:54.673
We get stinking rich, then make our
own ship and sail around the world.

59:57.510 --> 01:00:00.345
Aren't you going a little too fast?

01:00:00.638 --> 01:00:02.681
Do you know how old I am?

01:00:02.849 --> 01:00:04.808
Never mind, that's a secret.

01:00:04.976 --> 01:00:08.437
But I have got to go fast.

01:00:08.855 --> 01:00:15.360
You know, they... They say that
age kills the fire inside of a man.

01:00:15.778 --> 01:00:18.030
That he hears death coming.

01:00:18.197 --> 01:00:21.783
He opens the door and says,
"Come in. Give me rest."

01:00:21.993 --> 01:00:25.287
That is a pack of old damn lies.

01:00:25.455 --> 01:00:28.874
I've got enough fight in me
to devour the world.

01:00:29.042 --> 01:00:32.294
So I fight.

01:00:36.549 --> 01:00:39.343
Well? Do we?

01:00:40.053 --> 01:00:43.472
Or do we let the mountain win?

01:00:45.058 --> 01:00:46.475
Tell me what you need.

01:00:47.352 --> 01:00:51.313
I will need some strong wire,
hooks and... And things.

01:00:51.481 --> 01:00:53.482
I will have to go to town.

01:00:53.650 --> 01:00:57.069
I still have to figure out the angle.

01:00:57.236 --> 01:01:01.657
If it's not perfect,
it will be catastrophe.

01:01:05.078 --> 01:01:06.828
How long will it take you?

01:01:07.205 --> 01:01:08.747
Oh...

01:01:08.915 --> 01:01:12.334
The way things are going,
it had better be soon or not at all.

01:01:19.717 --> 01:01:21.093
I'll give you until Christmas.

01:01:23.596 --> 01:01:25.764
[CHURCH BELLS RINGING]

01:01:34.399 --> 01:01:36.274
[CHATTERING]

01:02:48.347 --> 01:02:50.348
[LAUGHING]

01:03:00.193 --> 01:03:01.902
[ZORBA SINGING IN THE DISTANCE]

01:03:24.675 --> 01:03:26.510
Hey, boss.

01:03:29.889 --> 01:03:30.889
[SNIFFS]

01:03:31.057 --> 01:03:32.891
Rose water.

01:03:46.906 --> 01:03:50.325
Boss?
Well? What news?

01:03:52.078 --> 01:03:54.704
I made a great discovery.

01:03:55.540 --> 01:03:58.750
Stones are alive.

01:03:58.918 --> 01:04:00.502
Well, that's fine.

01:04:01.420 --> 01:04:05.090
Well, I wish instead you'd discover
your famous angle.

01:04:05.258 --> 01:04:07.384
I'm trying, boss.

01:04:10.263 --> 01:04:11.680
[CLACKING SOUND]

01:04:16.936 --> 01:04:21.106
Look, your umbrella.
Never mind.

01:04:23.860 --> 01:04:26.778
Just let me remind you
that tomorrow's Christmas.

01:04:27.613 --> 01:04:29.030
I know.

01:04:38.583 --> 01:04:40.750
Wh...? Where are you going?

01:04:42.003 --> 01:04:44.004
I need some wire.

01:04:56.934 --> 01:04:59.436
Where the hell did I put it?

01:05:01.022 --> 01:05:03.148
Won't this string do?

01:05:06.068 --> 01:05:08.028
Excuse me.

01:05:12.533 --> 01:05:14.242
Look.

01:05:14.827 --> 01:05:16.494
A melomakarouna.

01:05:16.662 --> 01:05:19.247
A what?
A Christmas cookie.

01:05:19.415 --> 01:05:21.917
Well, what's so strange about that?

01:05:22.752 --> 01:05:24.502
Nothing.

01:05:25.463 --> 01:05:29.633
But many melomakarouna inside
an empty trunk is very strange.

01:05:29.800 --> 01:05:34.054
An umbrella under a bed is also strange.
All right, all right.

01:05:35.556 --> 01:05:38.850
She came here?
No. She sent them.

01:05:39.769 --> 01:05:43.313
Now you have the proof.
Now, it is very simple.

01:05:43.606 --> 01:05:48.068
Tonight, after Bouboulina's party...
Get on with your work.

01:05:52.531 --> 01:05:55.951
Boss, you want me
to beat you an egg?

01:05:56.118 --> 01:05:58.119
It's good for the strength.

01:06:00.289 --> 01:06:03.041
Boss, now I can tell you a secret.

01:06:03.209 --> 01:06:06.044
All these days I couldn't work,
I couldn't sleep.

01:06:06.212 --> 01:06:09.130
And you know why?
Because of the widow.

01:06:10.132 --> 01:06:13.468
Don't get me wrong, I know
she's too good for these old bones.

01:06:13.636 --> 01:06:16.805
But to think of her without anybody...

01:06:16.973 --> 01:06:18.682
...that was too much.

01:06:19.350 --> 01:06:24.062
All right, laugh, but remember this.

01:06:24.230 --> 01:06:29.067
If a woman sleeps alone,
it puts a shame on all men.

01:06:29.235 --> 01:06:31.236
God has a very big heart...

01:06:31.404 --> 01:06:34.823
...but there is one sin
he will not forgive:

01:06:34.991 --> 01:06:40.078
If a woman calls a man to her bed
and he will not go.

01:06:40.246 --> 01:06:44.541
I know, because a very wise,
old Turk told me.

01:06:46.544 --> 01:06:50.672
A Turk? And you,
a Greek, believed him?

01:07:02.852 --> 01:07:04.185
I'm going to wash.

01:07:05.855 --> 01:07:09.065
I thought the Greeks
and the Turks never talked.

01:07:09.442 --> 01:07:10.775
They just fought.

01:07:15.656 --> 01:07:18.241
Don't tell me you never went to war.

01:07:18.409 --> 01:07:20.952
I don't like that kind of stupid talk.

01:07:21.120 --> 01:07:22.454
What's so stupid about...

01:07:22.621 --> 01:07:25.582
...fighting for your country?
Excuse me, boss.

01:07:25.750 --> 01:07:30.128
You talk like a teacher.
You think like a teacher.

01:07:30.296 --> 01:07:32.547
How can you understand?

01:07:32.715 --> 01:07:34.758
Of course I can.

01:07:34.925 --> 01:07:37.093
With your head, yes.

01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:40.472
You say, "This is right.

01:07:40.973 --> 01:07:42.807
This is wrong."

01:07:43.893 --> 01:07:45.769
But when you talk...

01:07:46.062 --> 01:07:47.812
...I watch your arms...

01:07:47.980 --> 01:07:51.066
...your legs, your chest.

01:07:51.776 --> 01:07:53.485
They are dumb.

01:07:53.652 --> 01:07:55.278
They say nothing.

01:07:55.488 --> 01:07:59.657
So how can you understand?
You're just making up excuses.

01:07:59.825 --> 01:08:03.328
I don't believe you give
a damn about your country.

01:08:03.496 --> 01:08:06.122
Don't you talk to me like that!

01:08:06.832 --> 01:08:09.167
Look, here, and here and here.

01:08:09.335 --> 01:08:11.711
Nothing on the back!

01:08:15.674 --> 01:08:20.345
I have done things for my country
that would make your hair stand.

01:08:20.513 --> 01:08:25.015
I have killed, burned villages,
raped women.

01:08:25.184 --> 01:08:26.935
And why?

01:08:27.103 --> 01:08:30.354
Because they were Turks
or Bulgarians.

01:08:30.523 --> 01:08:33.274
That's the rotten damn fool I was.

01:08:35.694 --> 01:08:40.990
Now I look at a man, any man,
and I say, "He is good. He is bad."

01:08:41.158 --> 01:08:43.201
What do I care if he's Greek or Turk?

01:08:45.955 --> 01:08:49.040
As I get older,
I swear by the bread I eat.

01:08:49.250 --> 01:08:55.380
I even stop asking that.
Good or bad, what is the difference?

01:08:56.631 --> 01:08:59.259
They all end up the same way...

01:09:01.303 --> 01:09:03.888
...food for worms.

01:09:04.055 --> 01:09:06.140
[ZORBA CHUCKLES]

01:09:08.394 --> 01:09:12.397
And as for women,
you make fun of me that I love them.

01:09:12.564 --> 01:09:14.566
How can I not love them?

01:09:14.774 --> 01:09:17.652
They're such poor, weak creatures.

01:09:18.737 --> 01:09:20.654
And it takes so little.

01:09:22.198 --> 01:09:23.658
A man's hand on their breast...

01:09:24.076 --> 01:09:26.161
...and they give you all they've got.

01:09:36.337 --> 01:09:38.881
ZORBA:
Where are you, Bouboulina?

01:09:39.716 --> 01:09:42.051
Canavaro is here.

01:09:43.679 --> 01:09:45.930
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

01:09:48.434 --> 01:09:50.185
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

01:09:50.560 --> 01:09:52.770
Look what I brought you.

01:09:52.938 --> 01:09:53.938
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

01:09:54.106 --> 01:09:55.857
Happy Christmas.

01:09:56.734 --> 01:09:58.902
I made it myself
to make her feel good.

01:10:02.281 --> 01:10:03.489
[LAUGHS]

01:10:06.785 --> 01:10:08.411
Oh...

01:10:11.582 --> 01:10:13.708
It's me?
Yes.

01:10:13.876 --> 01:10:17.545
Merry Christmas, madame.
And also for you.

01:10:17.713 --> 01:10:21.716
What is that extraordinary smell
coming from the kitchen?

01:10:21.884 --> 01:10:25.762
It is a big fat Turkish.
A Turkish.

01:10:25.930 --> 01:10:31.601
Oh! I hope he's not burning.
Do not worry. Sit down.

01:10:31.769 --> 01:10:35.313
We will start from the center,
the belly.

01:10:35.481 --> 01:10:38.983
Then we will take care
of the other parts, later.

01:10:39.818 --> 01:10:41.569
Yes.

01:10:50.371 --> 01:10:51.996
[COUGHS LIGHTLY]

01:10:53.374 --> 01:10:55.500
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

01:11:01.340 --> 01:11:03.591
Aren't you feeling well?

01:11:07.805 --> 01:11:12.350
In my age, monsieur,
one is never well.

01:11:13.352 --> 01:11:16.145
Especially on the holidays.

01:11:17.898 --> 01:11:24.112
I drink to your health,
my beautiful chouchou mermaid.

01:11:24.280 --> 01:11:26.864
May you grow new teeth...

01:11:27.032 --> 01:11:29.617
...and new skin...

01:11:29.785 --> 01:11:33.871
...and throw away these stupid ribbons
you wear to hide your neck.

01:11:34.039 --> 01:11:36.291
[CATS MEOWING]

01:11:37.668 --> 01:11:40.795
May the Great Powers
come back to Crete.

01:11:40.963 --> 01:11:44.382
And when you rise out
of the waves to greet them...

01:11:44.550 --> 01:11:47.677
...may all their damn ships crash...

01:11:47.845 --> 01:11:52.515
...on these round, hard rocks.

01:11:52.683 --> 01:11:54.475
[BOTH LAUGH]

01:11:55.853 --> 01:12:00.189
I wish it could happen,
what you say.

01:12:00.357 --> 01:12:04.152
But it is too late.
No, it is not!

01:12:04.320 --> 01:12:05.653
[CATS MEOWING]

01:12:06.155 --> 01:12:07.572
[GROWLS]

01:12:07.740 --> 01:12:09.324
[GIGGLES]

01:12:12.578 --> 01:12:15.413
[ZORBA GROWLING
& HORTENSE LAUGHING]

01:12:15.914 --> 01:12:18.666
Please, no!

01:12:20.252 --> 01:12:21.919
[THUMPS]

01:12:34.933 --> 01:12:36.851
Are you all right?

01:12:37.936 --> 01:12:42.398
You see, it is too late.

01:12:46.904 --> 01:12:48.780
Up, up, up.

01:12:52.493 --> 01:12:57.622
Oh, don't be sad,
my little Bouboulina.

01:12:57.790 --> 01:13:00.291
I have heard of a new doctor
in Europe.

01:13:00.459 --> 01:13:03.419
He makes miracles.

01:13:03.796 --> 01:13:07.423
You take what the hell ever
he gives you, drops or powders...

01:13:07.633 --> 01:13:09.926
...and you become 20 again.

01:13:10.094 --> 01:13:12.512
Maybe 25.

01:13:12.930 --> 01:13:15.723
I will get you some.

01:13:16.809 --> 01:13:19.227
You will?
Sure.

01:13:19.603 --> 01:13:25.400
A big bottle?
A whole barrel.

01:13:26.777 --> 01:13:28.277
Here.

01:13:34.034 --> 01:13:36.577
What are you thinking?

01:13:38.163 --> 01:13:42.333
Alexandria, Beirut, Istanbul.

01:13:42.543 --> 01:13:44.544
How they loved me.

01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:46.295
Who?

01:13:47.756 --> 01:13:49.674
Everybody.

01:13:50.759 --> 01:13:54.095
Ali Bey, Mustafa Nahas Pasha.

01:13:54.346 --> 01:13:59.308
Suleiman Pasha. Especially Suleiman.

01:14:00.853 --> 01:14:03.938
[CATS SHRIEKING]

01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:10.987
Those damn cats.

01:14:20.164 --> 01:14:21.998
[CATS SHRIEKING]

01:14:33.343 --> 01:14:35.303
Well, I...
Shh.

01:14:36.054 --> 01:14:37.346
What?

01:14:38.599 --> 01:14:41.684
She's asleep?
Yes.

01:14:43.604 --> 01:14:45.188
Let her.

01:14:45.856 --> 01:14:48.149
She's 20 again.

01:14:48.650 --> 01:14:53.237
She's strolling
around Alexandria, Beirut.

01:14:54.239 --> 01:14:57.158
Look at her, smiling.

01:14:58.744 --> 01:15:02.079
Silly old bitch. Come on.

01:15:02.247 --> 01:15:04.248
We can't go
and just leave her alone.

01:15:04.416 --> 01:15:10.004
She's not alone. She is with
Suleiman Pasha, having hell of a time.

01:15:10.422 --> 01:15:12.632
Dirty old cow.

01:15:19.556 --> 01:15:21.933
[CHURCH BELLS RINGING]

01:15:29.233 --> 01:15:31.150
She is in.

01:15:31.360 --> 01:15:33.110
Go.

01:15:33.278 --> 01:15:35.446
And God bless you.

01:15:43.705 --> 01:15:45.540
Where are you going?
To church.

01:15:45.707 --> 01:15:48.251
I've never been to a Greek Christmas.
Oh, boss.

01:15:48.418 --> 01:15:51.379
No. Don't you understand?
Understand what?

01:15:51.547 --> 01:15:53.631
I understand you're young
and full of energy.

01:15:53.799 --> 01:15:56.050
I don't understand
what you're doing with it.

01:15:56.218 --> 01:15:57.760
[PASSERBY AND ZORBA
SPEAK IN GREEK]

01:15:57.928 --> 01:16:00.304
I've had enough of this.
Why don't you leave me alone?

01:16:00.472 --> 01:16:02.640
Because I love you,
and I want the best for you.

01:16:02.808 --> 01:16:04.976
Don't shout!
Who's shouting!

01:16:06.436 --> 01:16:09.939
There she is. She is waiting.

01:16:10.482 --> 01:16:12.483
Cigarette.
This is ridiculous.

01:16:12.651 --> 01:16:15.486
I'm not going to stand here arguing.
But, boss...

01:16:15.654 --> 01:16:19.657
...she is waiting for you.
Let's just say that I'm different...

01:16:19.825 --> 01:16:22.577
...and I've got to go my own way.

01:16:22.786 --> 01:16:25.496
If God went your way,
there would be no Christmas.

01:16:25.706 --> 01:16:30.001
He didn't go to church, he went to Mary.
And Christ was born.

01:16:30.210 --> 01:16:34.005
He went that way. Mary is the widow.

01:16:37.801 --> 01:16:40.094
[BOTH SPEAKING IN GREEK]

01:16:46.768 --> 01:16:49.812
On a deaf man's door,
you can knock forever!

01:16:49.980 --> 01:16:51.355
[CHUCKLES]

01:16:51.523 --> 01:16:53.107
Forever.

01:17:41.073 --> 01:17:43.908
[SINGING IN GREEK]

01:17:56.338 --> 01:17:59.256
Now, here's the money.
Thank you.

01:17:59.424 --> 01:18:02.343
And remember,
it's all I can afford.

01:18:02.511 --> 01:18:06.430
Poor boss, I know.
Just buy what we need for the cable...

01:18:06.598 --> 01:18:08.724
...and come straight back.
Of course.

01:18:08.892 --> 01:18:12.895
Don't get stuck anywhere on the way.
I will be quick like the wind.

01:18:13.063 --> 01:18:17.566
Five days. You promised.
Boss, I promise.

01:18:20.278 --> 01:18:22.238
Goodbye, boss.

01:18:23.240 --> 01:18:25.032
Zorba. Zorba!

01:18:27.327 --> 01:18:29.203
What do you want?

01:18:29.371 --> 01:18:31.080
Don't forget me.

01:18:31.248 --> 01:18:34.709
Yes. Goodbye.

01:18:40.716 --> 01:18:44.468
Don't be sad. He's coming back.

01:18:46.471 --> 01:18:48.973
They all say that.

01:20:03.673 --> 01:20:06.050
[CHATTERING]

01:20:08.637 --> 01:20:10.471
[CAR HORN HONKS]

01:20:27.572 --> 01:20:30.324
[BAND PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC]

01:21:14.578 --> 01:21:15.870
Hello, grandpa.

01:21:21.376 --> 01:21:26.964
Don't be scared.
I'm only doing my job.

01:21:28.466 --> 01:21:31.093
GarÃ§on! Champagne.

01:21:41.521 --> 01:21:49.320
[COOING]

01:22:03.752 --> 01:22:05.085
[SNAPS]

01:22:18.266 --> 01:22:19.516
[POPS]

01:22:36.034 --> 01:22:38.786
[PLAYING SOFT MELODY]

01:22:49.798 --> 01:22:51.048
[ZORBA SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:22:57.722 --> 01:22:58.973
[COUGHS]

01:23:20.120 --> 01:23:22.746
What's your name?
Grandpa.

01:23:22.914 --> 01:23:24.623
Come with me.

01:23:31.756 --> 01:23:33.257
[GIGGLES]

01:23:33.425 --> 01:23:36.051
[ZORBA GROWLS & LOLA LAUGHING]

01:23:41.391 --> 01:23:45.728
"I shall not describe you...

01:23:45.895 --> 01:23:48.939
...the continuation.

01:23:49.107 --> 01:23:51.442
Except to say...

01:23:51.651 --> 01:23:56.280
...that it was long and very wild."

01:23:56.448 --> 01:23:57.948
[CHUCKLES]

01:23:58.742 --> 01:24:00.242
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:24:01.786 --> 01:24:05.456
Very, very wild.

01:24:06.249 --> 01:24:07.583
Ah...

01:24:10.879 --> 01:24:13.172
Next afternoon...

01:24:14.549 --> 01:24:16.884
Next afternoon...

01:24:17.427 --> 01:24:19.428
...I wake up.

01:24:20.138 --> 01:24:21.805
And...

01:24:22.974 --> 01:24:24.475
...what do I see?

01:24:25.560 --> 01:24:28.812
Next to me, in bed...

01:24:33.985 --> 01:24:36.195
...the female sex...

01:24:36.988 --> 01:24:39.073
...in person.

01:24:43.203 --> 01:24:44.953
Soft...

01:24:47.749 --> 01:24:49.333
...and warm...

01:24:49.501 --> 01:24:53.337
...and sweet-smelling.

01:24:54.339 --> 01:24:57.299
So I say to myself:

01:24:58.426 --> 01:25:00.344
"Zorba...

01:25:01.721 --> 01:25:06.141
...you are in paradise.

01:25:08.770 --> 01:25:10.020
Enjoy it.

01:25:10.271 --> 01:25:13.107
Don't move."

01:25:15.360 --> 01:25:16.693
ZORBA:
Imagine what luck.

01:25:16.861 --> 01:25:18.612
There's a restaurant opposite...

01:25:18.780 --> 01:25:24.034
...and they sends us food,
splendiferous food. Caviar...

01:25:24.786 --> 01:25:28.372
...steaks, baklava, everything.

01:25:28.540 --> 01:25:34.628
We eat and back to work,
and back to sleep and so on, et cetera.

01:25:36.381 --> 01:25:38.340
Antoni!

01:25:39.843 --> 01:25:41.718
ZORBA:
This is my good news, boss.

01:25:41.886 --> 01:25:44.054
And don't worry,
I think of your business also.

01:25:44.264 --> 01:25:49.226
But I ask you, why push things?
Every day my head becomes more clear...

01:25:50.061 --> 01:25:53.063
...and I shall be able
to make the best deals.

01:25:53.273 --> 01:25:57.401
I kiss you friendly. Me, Zorba.

01:26:12.500 --> 01:26:14.710
ZORBA:
P.S., I forgot to tell you.

01:26:14.878 --> 01:26:17.421
Her name is Lola.

01:26:18.548 --> 01:26:23.177
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:26:30.435 --> 01:26:32.936
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:26:36.107 --> 01:26:37.900
Monsieur.

01:26:39.861 --> 01:26:44.781
Pardon. They told me
you had a letter.

01:26:46.618 --> 01:26:48.619
It's from him?

01:26:49.078 --> 01:26:51.121
It's from him.

01:26:56.794 --> 01:26:58.795
What does he say?

01:27:03.468 --> 01:27:05.469
Read it yourself.

01:27:21.611 --> 01:27:23.654
I cannot.

01:27:25.782 --> 01:27:27.241
My eyes.

01:27:32.372 --> 01:27:34.164
He says...

01:27:35.458 --> 01:27:37.501
...he's very busy.

01:27:41.005 --> 01:27:44.299
There is something for me?

01:27:44.509 --> 01:27:46.260
Of course.

01:27:47.637 --> 01:27:49.346
Read it.

01:27:50.848 --> 01:27:52.349
Please.

01:27:57.355 --> 01:28:01.608
"Please tell Bouboulina
that I miss her."

01:28:05.989 --> 01:28:07.781
Go on.

01:28:11.619 --> 01:28:13.370
"Tell her...

01:28:13.997 --> 01:28:17.916
...that every night I go back
to my little room...

01:28:18.918 --> 01:28:22.713
...and I pray to God
to send me back to her...

01:28:22.964 --> 01:28:24.631
...quickly.

01:28:29.887 --> 01:28:32.973
For without my Bouboulina...

01:28:33.433 --> 01:28:36.560
...I feel so damn miserable...

01:28:37.353 --> 01:28:40.147
...that when I see her again I...

01:28:41.232 --> 01:28:43.025
...I'll..."

01:28:45.069 --> 01:28:46.194
What?

01:28:48.948 --> 01:28:51.450
"I'll kneel before her...

01:28:52.577 --> 01:28:55.078
...and ask her to be mine forever."

01:28:59.542 --> 01:29:02.711
Forever?

01:29:02.879 --> 01:29:06.882
Yes, forever. That's what he says.

01:29:10.928 --> 01:29:12.721
All right.

01:29:13.556 --> 01:29:17.601
Tell him that I accept.

01:29:17.769 --> 01:29:22.064
And please, write that he brings me...

01:29:22.231 --> 01:29:25.067
...five meters of white satin...

01:29:25.234 --> 01:29:28.236
...and voile.

01:29:28.446 --> 01:29:32.199
You see, I cannot find here.

01:29:33.076 --> 01:29:35.452
I understand.

01:29:35.620 --> 01:29:37.871
You are very kind.

01:29:38.373 --> 01:29:39.873
Oh.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:43.251
One thing more.

01:29:46.130 --> 01:29:47.464
You know...

01:29:47.632 --> 01:29:52.719
...Zorba and me,
we like you very much.

01:29:53.096 --> 01:29:57.265
Will you be our witness?

01:29:58.101 --> 01:30:00.143
It will be an honor.

01:30:17.495 --> 01:30:18.954
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

01:30:52.280 --> 01:31:06.501
[SNIFFS]

01:32:04.101 --> 01:32:05.602
[STRUMS SANTOURI]

01:32:22.787 --> 01:32:25.455
[SINGING IN GREEK]

01:32:42.807 --> 01:32:43.974
Go away.

01:32:44.600 --> 01:32:45.684
For you.

01:32:47.270 --> 01:32:48.645
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:32:49.146 --> 01:32:51.314
[DOGS BARKING]

01:33:28.644 --> 01:33:30.979
[PLUCKING SANTOURI]

01:33:35.943 --> 01:33:37.277
[PLUCKS SANTOURI]

01:33:53.294 --> 01:34:00.842
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

01:34:08.309 --> 01:34:09.643
[WIDOW SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:34:10.353 --> 01:34:11.394
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:34:11.896 --> 01:34:13.772
[DOOR OPENS]

01:34:24.367 --> 01:34:25.700
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:34:54.689 --> 01:34:57.816
[MEN WHISPERING INAUDIBLY]

01:35:15.292 --> 01:35:17.711
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

01:35:25.344 --> 01:35:28.471
Lies! Lies! Lies!

01:35:50.661 --> 01:35:52.662
[SOBBING]

01:36:16.020 --> 01:36:17.771
I'm sorry.

01:36:18.314 --> 01:36:30.825
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:39:09.652 --> 01:39:11.194
[INDISTINCT VOICE YELLING]

01:40:12.214 --> 01:40:14.841
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:40:20.431 --> 01:40:23.683
[IN GREEK]
Are you her lover, too?

01:40:24.226 --> 01:40:27.562
[CROWD LAUGHING]

01:40:47.124 --> 01:40:49.250
[YELLS IN GREEK]

01:41:48.477 --> 01:41:51.354
[ZORBA HUMMING]

01:41:56.527 --> 01:41:57.860
Mr. Zorba.

01:42:00.322 --> 01:42:02.031
Boss!

01:42:03.033 --> 01:42:04.200
[LAUGHS]

01:42:04.827 --> 01:42:08.246
Oh, boss.

01:42:11.750 --> 01:42:13.501
You stink of perfume, Mr. Zorba.

01:42:13.669 --> 01:42:18.965
Yes, I know. I scrubbed my skin for
two hours, but it still smells. It's funny.

01:42:19.550 --> 01:42:21.300
Isn't it?

01:42:21.468 --> 01:42:22.802
Yes.

01:42:27.391 --> 01:42:29.058
Well, what's all this?

01:42:29.226 --> 01:42:31.185
Presents.
Presents!

01:42:31.353 --> 01:42:34.856
Who the hell for?
Barba Antoni, Yianni.

01:42:35.023 --> 01:42:36.482
This...

01:42:36.650 --> 01:42:41.404
...is for poor little Bouboulina.
I hope it's a wedding dress.

01:42:41.572 --> 01:42:42.905
A what?

01:42:43.532 --> 01:42:45.491
Well, you heard me.

01:42:48.245 --> 01:42:49.912
Boss...

01:42:50.789 --> 01:42:53.291
...what have you been cooking up?

01:42:55.669 --> 01:42:58.671
Well, she was here
when your letter came.

01:42:58.839 --> 01:43:02.341
I couldn't very well read to her
what was in it.

01:43:02.509 --> 01:43:03.843
Could I?

01:43:05.262 --> 01:43:08.097
That was not a very good joke, boss.

01:43:15.856 --> 01:43:18.274
What about the stuff
for the overhead cable?

01:43:18.442 --> 01:43:20.276
I got everything.

01:43:20.444 --> 01:43:21.694
Don't worry.

01:43:21.862 --> 01:43:23.279
Oh.

01:43:23.447 --> 01:43:25.198
A gift for you.

01:43:26.116 --> 01:43:30.077
A box of English chocolates.

01:43:32.414 --> 01:43:33.789
Thank you.

01:43:33.957 --> 01:43:35.583
It's all right.

01:43:38.295 --> 01:43:41.964
Hey, no more fooling around.

01:43:42.132 --> 01:43:43.633
Not in this place.

01:43:43.842 --> 01:43:47.470
Now we pull up our pants and we make
some money, a pile of money.

01:43:47.638 --> 01:43:49.472
[LAUGHS]

01:43:49.640 --> 01:43:51.641
You are incorrigible.

01:43:51.808 --> 01:43:54.143
[BOTH LAUGH]

01:43:54.436 --> 01:43:56.604
I don't know what that means,
but here.

01:43:56.813 --> 01:43:59.232
With my compliments.

01:44:01.235 --> 01:44:02.944
Good God.

01:44:03.153 --> 01:44:05.279
What have you done to your hair?

01:44:05.489 --> 01:44:07.865
I painted it.
Why?

01:44:08.408 --> 01:44:13.037
For pride. So I could go out with Lola,
without making her ashamed.

01:44:13.205 --> 01:44:14.872
[LAUGHING]

01:44:16.959 --> 01:44:21.003
He laughs.
But listen, you know what?

01:44:21.171 --> 01:44:24.840
I became young like my hair.

01:44:25.008 --> 01:44:26.926
Stronger than a bull.

01:44:27.094 --> 01:44:29.095
You ask Lola.

01:44:30.138 --> 01:44:32.848
And you know that pain
in my kidneys?

01:44:33.016 --> 01:44:34.600
That's gone.

01:44:34.768 --> 01:44:37.186
Ha, figure that out!

01:44:44.027 --> 01:44:45.486
By the way, boss...

01:44:45.654 --> 01:44:48.948
...I come in last night,
and you were out.

01:44:49.533 --> 01:44:52.201
Where the hell are you?

01:46:11.073 --> 01:46:13.491
[PROGRESSION SINGING HYMN]

01:47:33.613 --> 01:47:34.947
[MAN WHISTLES]

01:47:51.173 --> 01:47:53.883
[ALL SINGING HYMN]

01:48:03.852 --> 01:48:07.188
[YELLING AND WHISTLING COMING
FROM OUTSIDE]

01:48:22.162 --> 01:48:24.747
[MEN YELLING AND WHISTLING]

01:48:49.397 --> 01:48:50.648
[GRUNTS]

01:49:00.283 --> 01:49:02.409
[MIMITHOS YELLS IN GREEK]

01:49:04.955 --> 01:49:08.249
[CROWD YELLING AND SCREAMING
IN GREEK]

01:49:19.928 --> 01:49:21.262
Zorba!

01:49:21.429 --> 01:49:22.888
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:49:44.494 --> 01:49:46.495
[SCREAMS]

01:50:07.976 --> 01:50:09.518
[MAN SPEAKS IN GREEK]

01:51:04.074 --> 01:51:05.991
[MANOLAKAS YELLS IN GREEK]

01:51:13.416 --> 01:51:15.084
[ZORBA GRUNTS]

01:51:52.330 --> 01:51:53.956
Come with me.

01:52:03.466 --> 01:52:05.634
[WIDOW SCREAMING]

01:52:31.578 --> 01:52:33.579
[MIMITHOS CRIES AND YELLS]

01:52:50.138 --> 01:52:51.680
I...

01:52:52.432 --> 01:52:53.932
...couldn't help.

01:52:55.435 --> 01:52:58.020
[CRYING HYSTERICALLY]

01:53:07.822 --> 01:53:09.448
ZORBA:
Why do the young die?

01:53:11.034 --> 01:53:14.453
Why does anybody die? Tell me.

01:53:15.997 --> 01:53:17.915
I don't know.

01:53:18.666 --> 01:53:21.877
What's the use
of all your damn books?

01:53:22.045 --> 01:53:26.215
If they don't tell you that,
what the hell do they tell you?

01:53:28.426 --> 01:53:30.177
They tell me...

01:53:31.638 --> 01:53:34.348
...about the agony of men...

01:53:35.058 --> 01:53:38.018
...who can't answer
questions like yours.

01:53:42.524 --> 01:53:46.401
I spit on their agony.

01:54:20.520 --> 01:54:22.771
[THUNDER CRACKS]

01:54:38.788 --> 01:54:40.706
Who's that?

01:54:40.874 --> 01:54:42.791
It's me.

01:54:44.127 --> 01:54:47.296
Boss.
Get her inside, quickly.

01:54:50.425 --> 01:54:51.466
Hey.

01:55:02.270 --> 01:55:04.313
Did you get drenched?

01:55:08.526 --> 01:55:10.652
You are cruel.

01:55:12.447 --> 01:55:14.948
Why you abandon me?

01:55:15.658 --> 01:55:17.075
I will make some coffee.

01:55:20.663 --> 01:55:24.666
The whole village,
they're laughing at me.

01:55:26.127 --> 01:55:29.087
Where is my white satin?

01:55:30.089 --> 01:55:32.966
Where is my wedding dress?

01:55:35.595 --> 01:55:37.012
In Crete...

01:55:37.180 --> 01:55:40.682
...you don't find the real good satin.

01:55:40.850 --> 01:55:42.351
No!

01:55:43.353 --> 01:55:44.853
So...

01:55:45.688 --> 01:55:47.648
...I ordered some.

01:55:48.107 --> 01:55:49.650
From Athens.

01:55:49.817 --> 01:55:51.151
HORTENSE:
Yes.

01:55:51.319 --> 01:55:54.529
Also some white candles...

01:55:54.697 --> 01:55:56.365
...with silk ribbons.

01:55:56.574 --> 01:55:59.785
And pink bonbonniÃ¨res.

01:55:59.953 --> 01:56:01.161
[GIGGLES]

01:56:05.708 --> 01:56:07.876
Our wedding, my dear Bouboulina...

01:56:08.086 --> 01:56:10.170
...will be so splendiferous...

01:56:10.338 --> 01:56:12.381
...it will blind the world with glory.

01:56:12.590 --> 01:56:14.091
[GIGGLES]

01:56:15.885 --> 01:56:18.720
I can no longer keep it a secret.

01:56:21.557 --> 01:56:25.143
I have engaged
the best tailors in Athens...

01:56:25.311 --> 01:56:29.898
...to make for you a dress
like nobody has seen in the East.

01:56:30.066 --> 01:56:32.526
Or the West.

01:56:33.194 --> 01:56:37.155
Twenty meters of white satin
covered in pearls.

01:56:37.323 --> 01:56:41.910
With the sun on one breast
and the moon on the other.

01:56:42.078 --> 01:56:44.413
In pure gold.

01:56:50.378 --> 01:56:52.045
Me too.

01:56:54.132 --> 01:56:56.883
I have a secret for you.

01:57:11.024 --> 01:57:12.607
What's that?

01:57:14.027 --> 01:57:15.736
Open it.

01:57:17.780 --> 01:57:20.615
I'll have some coffee first.
No.

01:57:20.783 --> 01:57:22.242
Now.

01:57:27.623 --> 01:57:29.583
You see what you've done.

01:57:36.591 --> 01:57:38.759
Where the hell did you get these rings?

01:57:38.926 --> 01:57:41.219
I had them made for us.

01:57:41.387 --> 01:57:46.266
From two golden sovereign
the English admiral gave me.

01:57:46.934 --> 01:57:50.187
I was keeping them for my...

01:57:51.481 --> 01:57:52.814
For what?

01:57:54.817 --> 01:57:56.651
My funeral.

01:58:01.991 --> 01:58:03.658
Zorba?
Hm?

01:58:03.826 --> 01:58:06.495
Please. We become fiancÃ©s.

01:58:06.704 --> 01:58:08.288
Now.

01:58:08.748 --> 01:58:11.124
But...
We have the witness.

01:58:11.292 --> 01:58:13.627
We have the rings.

01:58:13.795 --> 01:58:15.504
Please?

01:58:15.713 --> 01:58:17.005
But we have no priest.

01:58:17.215 --> 01:58:19.424
I don't mind.

01:58:19.759 --> 01:58:21.927
God is watching.

01:58:22.929 --> 01:58:24.304
No?

01:58:26.974 --> 01:58:28.308
All right.

01:58:28.476 --> 01:58:31.853
We go outside
where God can see us better.

01:58:33.106 --> 01:58:35.482
You, you get ready.

01:58:35.650 --> 01:58:37.734
Witness, come on.

01:58:50.790 --> 01:58:52.707
What do we do?

01:58:53.543 --> 01:58:55.210
Can you sing?

01:58:55.378 --> 01:58:57.754
Certainly not.
Never mind, I can.

01:58:57.964 --> 01:59:00.966
Weddings, baptisms, funerals,
I know them back to front.

01:59:01.134 --> 01:59:03.301
I was a boy chanter.

01:59:09.016 --> 01:59:15.397
[ZORBA SINGING IN GREEK]

01:59:31.372 --> 01:59:33.415
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

01:59:57.398 --> 02:00:00.942
[COUGHING]

02:00:04.238 --> 02:00:05.864
It's nothing.

02:00:06.032 --> 02:00:08.033
Just a cold.

02:00:09.076 --> 02:00:11.745
Tomorrow you'll feel better.

02:00:13.873 --> 02:00:17.459
Next Sunday we go out,
have a hell of a time.

02:00:18.419 --> 02:00:20.462
It's Easter, you know.

02:00:21.297 --> 02:00:24.966
Yes.

02:00:30.806 --> 02:00:33.350
You need some sun to cheer you up.

02:00:43.361 --> 02:00:46.488
[MOUTHING]

02:00:54.163 --> 02:00:56.289
Now, my beautiful.

02:00:56.457 --> 02:00:59.167
We pull everything away.

02:00:59.794 --> 02:01:01.253
Listen to that...

02:01:01.420 --> 02:01:03.922
...beautiful noise.

02:01:04.173 --> 02:01:05.757
[BOTTLE POPS]

02:01:07.093 --> 02:01:08.260
Huh?

02:01:08.469 --> 02:01:09.511
[BOTTLE POPS]

02:01:09.804 --> 02:01:11.513
Like kissing.

02:01:13.307 --> 02:01:14.641
[BOTTLE POPS]

02:01:14.892 --> 02:01:16.434
Oh...

02:01:16.769 --> 02:01:18.687
...very sexy.

02:01:18.854 --> 02:01:20.188
[BOTTLE POPS]

02:01:22.191 --> 02:01:24.150
I'm jealous.

02:01:34.120 --> 02:01:35.870
[YELLS IN GREEK]

02:01:38.207 --> 02:01:40.917
[SPEAKS EXCITEDLY IN GREEK]

02:01:42.003 --> 02:01:44.129
[PLAYING UPBEAT MELODY]

02:01:55.308 --> 02:01:57.559
The foreigner is dying!

02:02:01.397 --> 02:02:03.064
She has no family!

02:02:03.232 --> 02:02:06.735
The state will take everything!

02:02:07.570 --> 02:02:10.947
Why not us? We're the poor!

02:02:22.835 --> 02:02:25.754
Murderers! Killers!

02:02:31.469 --> 02:02:32.761
[MOANS]

02:02:34.972 --> 02:02:36.264
ZORBA:
Shh.

02:03:07.546 --> 02:03:09.422
I don't want...
No, no.

02:03:09.590 --> 02:03:12.926
I don't know what...
It's all right. It's all right.

02:03:13.094 --> 02:03:14.594
[HORTENSE SOBBING]

02:03:14.970 --> 02:03:16.721
ZORBA:
Shh, shh, shh.

02:03:24.063 --> 02:03:27.482
[CLAMORING]

02:03:32.154 --> 02:03:33.154
[GASPS]

02:03:35.658 --> 02:03:39.119
[FOOTSTEPS AND
LOUD TALKING OUTSIDE]

02:03:53.092 --> 02:03:55.510
Shh. Yes.

02:03:57.805 --> 02:03:59.597
[WHISPERING INAUDIBLY]

02:04:05.062 --> 02:04:07.355
[WHISPERING IN GREEK]

02:04:19.160 --> 02:04:22.662
[MUTTERING IN FRENCH]

02:04:26.459 --> 02:04:37.886
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

02:04:47.229 --> 02:04:53.610
Canavaro.

02:05:12.338 --> 02:05:15.423
[WOMEN WAILING]

02:05:16.842 --> 02:05:18.760
[SCREAMING IN FRENCH]

02:05:21.347 --> 02:05:23.765
[ZORBA SPEAKING IN GREEK]

02:05:33.025 --> 02:05:36.110
It's me, Zorba.

02:05:37.154 --> 02:05:39.030
Don't be afraid.

02:06:20.406 --> 02:06:23.700
[WOMEN YELLING]

02:07:06.827 --> 02:07:09.203
[CLAMORING]

02:08:09.932 --> 02:08:11.349
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

02:08:13.936 --> 02:08:16.771
He asks us to drink
to her soul.

02:09:23.255 --> 02:09:25.631
[CROWD CLAMORING]

02:09:29.011 --> 02:09:32.263
Zorba, what about the funeral?

02:09:32.598 --> 02:09:34.766
There will be no funeral.

02:09:35.309 --> 02:09:36.768
Why?

02:09:36.935 --> 02:09:38.853
She was a Frank.

02:09:39.021 --> 02:09:42.190
She crossed herself
with four fingers.

02:09:44.276 --> 02:09:46.360
But I don't understand.

02:09:47.196 --> 02:09:50.531
The priest will not bury her
like everybody else.

02:09:50.949 --> 02:09:53.367
But that's dreadful.
Why?

02:09:53.535 --> 02:09:55.620
She is dead.

02:09:55.788 --> 02:09:58.039
It makes no difference.

02:10:48.841 --> 02:10:50.758
[CHEERING]

02:11:12.698 --> 02:11:14.574
Hey, boss!

02:11:14.741 --> 02:11:16.117
Boss!

02:11:16.285 --> 02:11:18.244
Come on. We are nearly ready.

02:11:18.412 --> 02:11:21.122
Hey, Canavaro,
you want to come and watch too?

02:11:24.126 --> 02:11:25.710
Whoa!

02:11:26.211 --> 02:11:27.962
Come on.

02:11:31.258 --> 02:11:34.135
[PEOPLE CHANTING HYMN]

02:11:47.149 --> 02:11:49.233
[PRIEST AND ZORBA SPEAKING
IN GREEK]

02:11:50.819 --> 02:11:53.154
In the name of the Father!

02:11:55.991 --> 02:11:57.575
[GUNSHOT]

02:12:06.001 --> 02:12:07.585
[CROWD MUTTERING IN GREEK]

02:12:47.876 --> 02:12:50.211
It's nothing. It's nothing!

02:12:50.379 --> 02:12:52.505
The first time it always does that.

02:12:52.673 --> 02:12:54.882
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

02:12:58.553 --> 02:13:00.680
And the Son!

02:13:00.889 --> 02:13:02.848
Hey! Hey!

02:13:03.016 --> 02:13:04.225
[GUNSHOT]

02:13:13.819 --> 02:13:15.528
[CROWD CLAMORING]

02:13:41.263 --> 02:13:43.764
[CHATTERING]

02:13:46.268 --> 02:13:48.019
Boss, where are you, boss?

02:13:48.186 --> 02:13:49.520
It's nothing.

02:13:49.730 --> 02:13:52.940
[ZORBA SPEAKING IN GREEK]

02:13:55.569 --> 02:13:57.028
And the Holy Ghost!

02:13:58.905 --> 02:14:00.614
[GUNSHOT]

02:14:23.138 --> 02:14:24.180
[SQUAWKING]

02:14:28.101 --> 02:14:29.977
[CROWD SCREAMING]

02:15:09.851 --> 02:15:11.852
[MUTTERING]

02:15:49.850 --> 02:15:53.561
Hey, Canavaro. How are you?

02:15:57.357 --> 02:15:58.691
The lamb!
What?

02:15:58.859 --> 02:16:00.568
It will burn!

02:16:47.199 --> 02:16:48.699
You know...

02:16:48.867 --> 02:16:51.619
...people tell the future from this.

02:16:52.745 --> 02:16:54.370
Can you?

02:16:55.207 --> 02:16:56.874
Everything's fine.

02:16:57.041 --> 02:16:59.834
We will live a thousand years.

02:17:00.879 --> 02:17:03.422
Oh, I see a journey.

02:17:03.590 --> 02:17:06.258
A big journey to a city.

02:17:06.425 --> 02:17:08.802
With big houses.

02:17:15.559 --> 02:17:17.477
How soon, boss?

02:17:18.480 --> 02:17:20.272
I don't know.

02:17:20.815 --> 02:17:22.148
A few days.

02:17:24.361 --> 02:17:26.153
What will I do...

02:17:26.321 --> 02:17:27.780
...without your company?

02:17:27.989 --> 02:17:29.573
Cheer up.

02:17:30.367 --> 02:17:32.618
We'll get together again.

02:17:32.994 --> 02:17:34.327
No.

02:17:34.495 --> 02:17:36.914
You'll go away and stay.

02:17:37.082 --> 02:17:39.250
With your books.

02:17:40.877 --> 02:17:42.585
Your health.

02:17:43.922 --> 02:17:46.173
Yours, Zorba.

02:17:47.842 --> 02:17:49.343
[CHUCKLES]

02:17:51.638 --> 02:17:55.266
Damn it, boss,
I like you too much not to say it.

02:17:55.433 --> 02:17:57.017
You've got everything...

02:17:57.184 --> 02:18:01.021
...except one thing: Madness.

02:18:01.189 --> 02:18:04.358
A man needs a little madness,
or else...

02:18:05.192 --> 02:18:06.527
Or else?

02:18:06.695 --> 02:18:10.447
He never dares cut the rope
and be free.

02:18:20.709 --> 02:18:22.709
Are you angry with me?

02:18:32.679 --> 02:18:34.638
Teach me to dance.

02:18:35.514 --> 02:18:37.057
Will you?

02:18:38.559 --> 02:18:40.394
Dance?

02:18:42.814 --> 02:18:45.983
Did you say dance?

02:18:49.236 --> 02:18:51.155
Come on, my boy.

02:18:51.323 --> 02:18:53.490
[SNAPPING FINGERS]

02:18:59.456 --> 02:19:01.165
Together.

02:19:10.091 --> 02:19:11.258
Let's go.

02:19:11.425 --> 02:19:12.718
Whoop.

02:19:12.886 --> 02:19:14.594
[LAUGHS]

02:19:19.726 --> 02:19:20.768
Again.

02:19:20.934 --> 02:19:22.269
Whoop.

02:19:27.525 --> 02:19:29.401
[LAUGHS]

02:19:31.111 --> 02:19:32.737
Down.

02:19:36.910 --> 02:19:38.786
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

02:19:41.456 --> 02:19:42.956
Boss...

02:19:43.124 --> 02:19:45.084
...I have so much
to tell you.

02:19:47.087 --> 02:19:50.798
I never loved a man more than you.

02:19:51.007 --> 02:19:53.384
[SNAPPING FINGERS]

02:19:59.432 --> 02:20:00.808
Whoop.

02:20:03.812 --> 02:20:05.229
Hey, boss...

02:20:05.397 --> 02:20:09.650
...did you ever see
a more splendiferous crash?

02:20:11.611 --> 02:20:17.074
[LAUGHING]

02:20:22.997 --> 02:20:24.498
You can laugh too, huh?

02:20:24.666 --> 02:20:27.251
Hey, you laugh!

02:20:29.546 --> 02:20:33.298
You saw...
You saw how they all ran.

02:20:34.134 --> 02:20:37.344
Especially the monks.

02:20:39.347 --> 02:20:41.181
The second time...

02:20:41.349 --> 02:20:44.017
The third time was the best.

02:20:44.185 --> 02:20:46.353
Nothing left!

02:20:47.021 --> 02:20:48.856
Hey!
Nothing.

02:20:51.317 --> 02:20:53.360
[SINGING IN GREEK]

02:20:53.570 --> 02:20:55.654
Whoop. Whoop!

02:20:55.947 --> 02:20:59.032
Whoop! Whoop! Whoop!

02:21:59.594 --> 02:22:01.595
[English - US - PSDH]
